Document: TextureRect
Path: godot/classes/class_texturerect.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the TextureRect node, including expansion mode, flipping, mouse filtering, stretch mode, and the texture itself.

Properties
* expand_mode (ExpandMode): Controls how the texture is scaled to fit the control's rectangle. Default: 0.
* flip_h (bool): If true, the texture is flipped horizontally. Default: false.
* flip_v (bool): If true, the texture is flipped vertically. Default: false.
* mouse_filter (MouseFilter): Controls how mouse events are handled. Default: 1 (overrides Control.mouse_filter).
* stretch_mode (StretchMode): Controls how the texture is stretched or tiled within the control's rectangle. Default: 0.
* texture (Texture2D): The texture to display.
---CHUNK---
Document: TextureRect
Path: godot/classes/class_texturerect.rst
Summary: Defines enumerations for controlling how a TextureRect expands and stretches its texture.

Enumerations
ExpandMode:
  EXPAND_KEEP_SIZE = 0: The minimum size will be equal to texture size, i.e. TextureRect can't be smaller than the texture.
  EXPAND_IGNORE_SIZE = 1: The size of the texture won't be considered for minimum size calculation, so the TextureRect can be shrunk down past the texture size.
  EXPAND_FIT_WIDTH = 2: The height of the texture will be ignored. Minimum width will be equal to the current height. Useful for horizontal layouts, e.g. inside HBoxContainer.
  EXPAND_FIT_WIDTH_PROPORTIONAL = 3: Same as EXPAND_FIT_WIDTH, but keeps texture's aspect ratio.
  EXPAND_FIT_HEIGHT = 4: The width of the texture will be ignored. Minimum height will be equal to the current width. Useful for vertical layouts, e.g. inside VBoxContainer.
  EXPAND_FIT_HEIGHT_PROPORTIONAL = 5: Same as EXPAND_FIT_HEIGHT, but keeps texture's aspect ratio.

StretchMode:
  STRETCH_SCALE = 0: Scale to fit the node's bounding rectangle.
  STRETCH_TILE = 1: Tile inside the node's bounding rectangle. Note: STRETCH_TILE mode is not supported for texture set to an AtlasTexture with non-zero AtlasTexture.margin.
  STRETCH_KEEP = 2: The texture keeps its original size and stays in the bounding rectangle's top-left corner.
  STRETCH_KEEP_CENTERED = 3: The texture keeps its original size and stays centered in the node's bounding rectangle.
  STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT = 4: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, but maintain the texture's aspect ratio.
  STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_CENTERED = 5: Scale the texture to fit the node's bounding rectangle, center it and maintain its aspect ratio.
  STRETCH_KEEP_ASPECT_COVERED = 6: Scale the texture so that the shorter side fits the bounding rectangle. The other side clips to the node's limits.
---CHUNK---
Document: TextureRect
Path: godot/classes/class_texturerect.rst
Summary: Describes the properties of the TextureRect node, including how the texture is expanded, flipped, stretched, and the texture resource itself.

Property: expand_mode (ExpandMode)
Description: Defines how minimum size is determined based on the texture's size. Default: 0.
Note: Using EXPAND_FIT_WIDTH, EXPAND_FIT_WIDTH_PROPORTIONAL, EXPAND_FIT_HEIGHT, or EXPAND_FIT_HEIGHT_PROPORTIONAL may result in unstable behavior in some Container controls. This behavior may be re-evaluated and changed in the future.
Method: set_expand_mode(value: ExpandMode)
Method: get_expand_mode() -> ExpandMode

Property: flip_h (bool)
Description: If true, texture is flipped horizontally. Default: false.
Method: set_flip_h(value: bool)
Method: is_flipped_h() -> bool

Property: flip_v (bool)
Description: If true, texture is flipped vertically. Default: false.
Method: set_flip_v(value: bool)
Method: is_flipped_v() -> bool

Property: stretch_mode (StretchMode)
Description: Controls the texture's behavior when resizing the node's bounding rectangle. Default: 0.
Method: set_stretch_mode(value: StretchMode)
Method: get_stretch_mode() -> StretchMode

Property: texture (Texture2D)
Description: The node's Texture2D resource.
Method: set_texture(value: Texture2D)
Method: get_texture() -> Texture2D